revisions.description: 1. Added ccmeEphonePrimaryDn in ccmeEphoneConfTable. 2. Deprecated ciscoCcmeMIBComplianceRev1 and added ciscoCcmeMIBComplianceRev2 MODULE-COMPLIANCE. 3. Added ccmeActiveStatsGroupEM.
1. Add ccmeEphonePrimaryDn in ccmeEphoneConfTable. 2. Deprecated ciscoCcmeMIBCompliance and added ciscoCcmeMIBComplianceRev1 MODULE-COMPLIANCE. 3. Added ccmeConfigGroup1.
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoCcmeMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ccme-srst@cisco.com
ciscoCcmeMIB.description: This MIB allows management of Cisco CallManager Express (CCME) feature in Cisco IOS. CCME is optional software feature that enables Cisco routers to deliver Key System or Hybrid PBX functionality for enterprise branch offices or small businesses.

CcmeDigitPatternString.name: CcmeDigitPatternString
CcmeDigitPatternString.description: A E.164 address string limited to the character set '0123456789*#.+ABCDT'. An address of length zero indicates that no address is specified.

CcmeNightServiceCodeString.name: CcmeNightServiceCodeString
CcmeNightServiceCodeString.description: A code string limited to character set '0123456789*' This code begins with first character as * (asteric) and followed by at least one digit. Example - *9234 Users enters at an IP phone to disable or enable night service.

ccmeEnabled.name: ccmeEnabled
ccmeEnabled.description: Indicates whether the Cisco CallManager Express feature is enabled on the device. 'true' means that the CCME feature is enabled on this device. 'false' means that the CCME feature is disabled.

ccmeVersion.name: ccmeVersion
ccmeVersion.description: The version of Cisco CallManager Express on the device.

ccmeIPAddressType.name: ccmeIPAddressType
ccmeIPAddressType.description: Address type of ccmeIPAddress. Only IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are expected.

ccmeIPAddress.name: ccmeIPAddress
ccmeIPAddress.description: Indicates the IP address through which the IP phones communicate with CCME. The type of this address is determined by the value of the ccmeSysIPAddressType object. This IP address is usually the IP address bound to the Ethernet port on the gateway to which the phones are connected.

ccmePortNumber.name: ccmePortNumber
ccmePortNumber.description: This object indicates the TCP port number to use for Skinny Client Control Protocol (SCCP). This port also indicates through which IP phones communicate with this device.

ccmeMaxEphones.name: ccmeMaxEphones
ccmeMaxEphones.description: Maximum number of IP phones allowed by the configuration for the Cisco CallManager Express on the device. Maximum permissible range is IOS version and platform dependent. A value of zero indicates no IP phones are permitted to register to this device.

ccmeMaxDirectoryNumber.name: ccmeMaxDirectoryNumber
ccmeMaxDirectoryNumber.description: This object indicates the maximum number of IP phones extensions (ephone-dns) or directory numbers supported by this device. Maximum permissible range is IOS version and platform dependent. A value of zero indicates no IP phones extensions could be created.

ccmeMaxConferences.name: ccmeMaxConferences
ccmeMaxConferences.description: Maximum number of simultaneous three-party conferences supported by the Cisco CallManager Express on the device. Range is IOS version and platform dependent. With CCME Version 3.1, the following are the maximum values for each platform - Cisco 1750, Cisco 1751, Cisco 2600, Cisco 3640 - 8 conferences. Cisco 3660, Cisco 3725, Cisco 3745 - 16 conferences. Default is half the maximum number of simultaneous three-party conferences for each platform. A value of zero indicates no three-party conferences allowed on this device.

ccmeMaxRedirect.name: ccmeMaxRedirect
ccmeMaxRedirect.description: Indicates the maximum number of times that a call can be redirected by call forwarding or transfer within this device.

ccmeScriptName.name: ccmeScriptName
ccmeScriptName.description: This object indicates the session-level IVR application script in Tool Command Language (TCL) for all extensions (ephone-dns) in CCME system. By default no application script is selected for all extensions and the object length in this case will return a zero length string.

ccmeVoiceMailNumber.name: ccmeVoiceMailNumber
ccmeVoiceMailNumber.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone number that is associated with a voice-mail (speed-dial) on this device. If voice-mail number is not configured, this object has a length of zero.

ccmeMwiRelay.name: ccmeMwiRelay
ccmeMwiRelay.description: Indicates whether the device can relay message-waiting indication (MWI) notification to remote Cisco IP phones.

ccmeMwiExpires.name: ccmeMwiExpires
ccmeMwiExpires.description: Expiration time in seconds, for the registration of the message-waiting indication (MWI) client or server. Range is 600 to 99999.

ccmeTransferSystem.name: ccmeTransferSystem
ccmeTransferSystem.description: This object indicates the call transfer method for all configured Cisco IP phone extensions, that use the ITU-T H.450.2 standard. Call transfers that use the H.450.2 standard can be 'blind' or 'consultative'. A blind transfer is one in which the transferring extension connects the caller to a destination extension before ringback begins. A consultative transfer is one in which the transferring party either connects the caller to a ringing phone (ringback heard) or speaks with the third party before connecting the caller to the third party. blind - Calls are transferred without consultation using a single phone line and the Cisco proprietary method. localConsult - Calls are transferred with local consultation using the second phone line if available, or the calls fall back to blind for nonlocal consultation or transfer target. This mode is intended for use primarily in voice over Frame Relay networks. fullBlind - Calls are transferred without consultation using H.450.2 standard method. fullConsult - Calls are transferred using H.450.2 with consultation using the second phone line if available, or the calls fall back to fullBlind if the second line is unavailable.

ccmeTimeFormat.name: ccmeTimeFormat
ccmeTimeFormat.description: Time display format on Cisco IP phones in a Cisco CallManager Express system. twelve(1) - 12 hour clock. twentyfour(2) - 24 hour clock.

ccmeDateFormat.name: ccmeDateFormat
ccmeDateFormat.description: Indicates the date display format on Cisco IP phones in a Cisco CallManager Express system.

ccmeUrlforServicesBtn.name: ccmeUrlforServicesBtn
ccmeUrlforServicesBtn.description: This object indicates the URL information for the 'Services' button on the Cisco IP phone display. The Cisco IP Phone 7940 and Cisco IP phone 7960 can support four URL's in association with the four programmable feature buttons on those IP phones - Directories, Information, Messages and Services. The fifth button, Settings, is managed entirely by the phone. Operation of these services is determined by the Cisco IP phone capabilities and the content of the referenced URL.

ccmeUrlforDirectoriesBtn.name: ccmeUrlforDirectoriesBtn
ccmeUrlforDirectoriesBtn.description: This object indicates the URL information for the 'Directories' button on the Cisco IP phone display. The Cisco IP Phone 7940 and Cisco IP phone 7960 can support four URL's in association with the four programmable feature buttons on those IP phones - Directories, Information, Messages and Services. The fifth button, Settings, is managed entirely by the phone. Operation of these services is determined by the Cisco IP phone capabilities and the content of the referenced URL.

ccmeMohFlashFile.name: ccmeMohFlashFile
ccmeMohFlashFile.description: This object indicates the name of the audio file to use for the Music on hold (MOH) audio stream. Audio files that are used for MOH exist in the flash file system on the device. A MOH file can be .au or .wav file format. However, the file format must contain 8-bit 8-KHz data in a-law or mu-law. Maximum length of filename is 128 characters long. This object returns a zero length string if the MOH from flash is not configured on this router.

ccmeMohMulticastFromFlashEnabled.name: ccmeMohMulticastFromFlashEnabled
ccmeMohMulticastFromFlashEnabled.description: Indicates whether music-on-hold (MOH) multicast from flash file source is enabled or disabled on this router. If ccmeMohFlashFile is zero length this object has no relevance.

ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddrType.name: ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddrType
ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddrType.description: Address type of ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddr. Only IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are expected.

ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddr.name: ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddr
ccmeMohFlashMulticastIPAddr.description: This object indicates the destination IP address for multicast of the audio stream from Flash file, that is designated for MOH. If ccmeMohFlashFile is zero length this object has no relevance. Cisco IP phones don not support multicast at 224.x.x.x addresses.

ccmeMohFlashMulticastPortNum.name: ccmeMohFlashMulticastPortNum
ccmeMohFlashMulticastPortNum.description: This object indicates the media port for multicast of the audio stream from Flash file that is designated for MOH. This object has no relevance if ccmeMohMulticastFromFlash object is zero length.

ccmePhoneFirmwareTable.name: ccmePhoneFirmwareTable
ccmePhoneFirmwareTable.description: A list of firmware load configured for each IP Phone on this device.

ccmePhoneFirmwareEntry.name: ccmePhoneFirmwareEntry
ccmePhoneFirmwareEntry.description: Information on an Cisco IP phone type and its configured firmware load. There is an entry in this table for each IP Phone type firmware that is configured on this device.

ccmePhoneFirmwareIndex.name: ccmePhoneFirmwareIndex
ccmePhoneFirmwareIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmePhoneFirmwareEntry.

ccmePhoneType.name: ccmePhoneType
ccmePhoneType.description: Type or model of Cisco IP phone. Cisco IP Phone types are 7902, 7905, 7910, 7912, 7914, 7920, 7935, 7936, 7940, 7960, ATA-186, ATA-188

ccmePhoneFirmwareRev.name: ccmePhoneFirmwareRev
ccmePhoneFirmwareRev.description: The vendor-specific firmware revision string configured for the Cisco IP phone on this device.

ccmeTransferPatternTable.name: ccmeTransferPatternTable
ccmeTransferPatternTable.description: A list of transfer patterns configured on this device.

ccmeTransferPatternEntry.name: ccmeTransferPatternEntry
ccmeTransferPatternEntry.description: Information on a transfer pattern configured. There is an entry in this table for each transfer pattern that is configured on this device.

ccmeTransferPatternIndex.name: ccmeTransferPatternIndex
ccmeTransferPatternIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeTransferPatternEntry.

ccmeTransferPattern.name: ccmeTransferPattern
ccmeTransferPattern.description: String of digits for permitted call transfers.

ccmeTransferPatternType.name: ccmeTransferPatternType
ccmeTransferPatternType.description: Indicates the pattern for call transfer. 'blind(1)' indicates blind transfer pattern. 'h4502(2)' indicates H.450.2 consultative call transfer.

ccmeWebGUIEditEnabled.name: ccmeWebGUIEditEnabled
ccmeWebGUIEditEnabled.description: Indicates Cisco CallManager Express web-based Graphical User Interface (GUI) is allowed to add extensions (ephone-dns).

ccmeWebGUITimeEnabled.name: ccmeWebGUITimeEnabled
ccmeWebGUITimeEnabled.description: Indicates Cisco CallManager Express web-based Graphical User Interface (GUI) is allowed to change or set time on this device.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternTable.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternTable
ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternTable.description: A list of after hour block patterns configured on this device.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternEntry.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternEntry
ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternEntry.description: Information about a configured after hours block pattern. There is an entry in this table for each after hours block that is configured on this device.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternTag.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternTag
ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternTag.description: An unique identifier tag configured for a pattern.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockPattern.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockPattern
ccmeAfterHrsBlockPattern.description: Indicates the configured string of outgoing call digits that will be matched for blocking call at specified after hours. Example - 9011

ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternAllTime.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternAllTime
ccmeAfterHrsBlockPatternAllTime.description: Indicates whether after hours block pattern is applicable all time. 'true' means ccmeAfterHrsBlockPattern pattern will always be applied, 7 days a week, 24 hours a day. 'false' means ccmeAfterHrsBlockPattern pattern will be blocked during the days and dates defined by ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateTable and ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayTable objects.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateTable.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateTable
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateTable.description: A list of recurring time period based on date during which outgoing calls that match defined block patterns are blocked on IP phones.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateEntry.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateEntry
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateEntry.description: Information on a configured after hour block pattern date. There is an entry in this table for each entry that is configured on this device. An entry is deleted from this table once an after hour block configuration is removed from this device.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateIndex.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateIndex
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeAfterHrsBlockDateEntry.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateMonth.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateMonth
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateMonth.description: Indicates the month of the year during which the 'after hours block' service is active.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDate.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDate
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDate.description: Indicates the day of the month during which the 'after hours block' service is activated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartHour.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartHour
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartHour.description: Indicates the hour of the day during which the 'after hours block' service is activated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartMin.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartMin
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStartHour from which the 'after hours block' service is activated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopHour.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopHour
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopHour.description: Indicates the hour of the day during which during which the 'after hours block' service is deactivated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopMin.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopMin
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeAfterHrsBlockDateStopHour after which the 'after hours block' service is deactivated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayTable.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayTable
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayTable.description: A list of recurring time period based on day of week during which outgoing calls that match defined block patterns are blocked on IP phones.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayEntry.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayEntry
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayEntry.description: Information on a configured after hour block pattern day. There is an entry in this table for each entry that is configured on this device. An entry is deleted from this table once an 'after hour block' day configuration is removed from this device.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayIndex.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayIndex
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeAfterHrsBlockDayEntry.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDay.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDay
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDay.description: Indicates the day of the week during which the 'after hours block' service is active.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartHour.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartHour
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartHour.description: Indicates the hour of the day during which the 'after hours block' service is activated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartMin.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartMin
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStartHour from which the 'after hours block' service is activated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopHour.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopHour
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopHour.description: Indicates the hour of the day during which during which the 'after hours block' service is deactivated.

ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopMin.name: ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopMin
ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeAfterHrsBlockDayStopHour after which the 'after hours block' service is deactivated.

ccmeNightServiceCode.name: ccmeNightServiceCode
ccmeNightServiceCode.description: Indicates the configured night service code that disables or enables night service on IP phones. The code is the digit code that a user enters at an IP phone to disable or enable night service. The code begins with '*' (asterisk).

ccmeNightServiceDateTable.name: ccmeNightServiceDateTable
ccmeNightServiceDateTable.description: A list of recurring time period based on date of month during which night service is active.

ccmeNightServiceDateEntry.name: ccmeNightServiceDateEntry
ccmeNightServiceDateEntry.description: Information on a configured night service date pattern. There is an entry in this table for each entry that is configured on this device. An entry is deleted from this table once a night service configuration is removed from this device.

ccmeNightServiceDateIndex.name: ccmeNightServiceDateIndex
ccmeNightServiceDateIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeNightServiceDateEntry.

ccmeNightServiceDateMonth.name: ccmeNightServiceDateMonth
ccmeNightServiceDateMonth.description: Indicates the month of the year during which the night service is active.

ccmeNightServiceDate.name: ccmeNightServiceDate
ccmeNightServiceDate.description: Indicates the day of the month during which the night service is activated.

ccmeNightServiceDateStartHour.name: ccmeNightServiceDateStartHour
ccmeNightServiceDateStartHour.description: Indicates the hour of the date during which the night service is activated.

ccmeNightServiceDateStartMin.name: ccmeNightServiceDateStartMin
ccmeNightServiceDateStartMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeNightServiceDateStartHour during which the night service is activated.

ccmeNightServiceDateStopHour.name: ccmeNightServiceDateStopHour
ccmeNightServiceDateStopHour.description: Indicates the hour of the date during which during which the night service is deactivated.

ccmeNightServiceDateStopMin.name: ccmeNightServiceDateStopMin
ccmeNightServiceDateStopMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeNightServiceDateStopHour during which the night service is deactivated.

ccmeNightServiceDayTable.name: ccmeNightServiceDayTable
ccmeNightServiceDayTable.description: A list of recurring time period associated with a day of the week during which night service is active.

ccmeNightServiceDayEntry.name: ccmeNightServiceDayEntry
ccmeNightServiceDayEntry.description: Information on a configured night service day pattern. There is an entry in this table for each entry that is configured on this device. An entry is deleted from this table once a night service configuration is removed from this device.

ccmeNightServiceDayIndex.name: ccmeNightServiceDayIndex
ccmeNightServiceDayIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeNightServiceDayEntry.

ccmeNightServiceDay.name: ccmeNightServiceDay
ccmeNightServiceDay.description: Indicates the day of the week during which the night service is active.

ccmeNightServiceDayStartHour.name: ccmeNightServiceDayStartHour
ccmeNightServiceDayStartHour.description: Indicates the hour of the day during which the night service is activated.

ccmeNightServiceDayStartMin.name: ccmeNightServiceDayStartMin
ccmeNightServiceDayStartMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeNightServiceDayStartHour during which the night service is activated.

ccmeNightServiceDayStopHour.name: ccmeNightServiceDayStopHour
ccmeNightServiceDayStopHour.description: Indicates the hour of the day during which during which the night service is deactivated.

ccmeNightServiceDayStopMin.name: ccmeNightServiceDayStopMin
ccmeNightServiceDayStopMin.description: Indicates the minute in the ccmeNightServiceDayStopHour during which the night service is deactivated.

ccmeFXOHookFlashEnabled.name: ccmeFXOHookFlashEnabled
ccmeFXOHookFlashEnabled.description: Indicates whether Flash soft key display on IP Phone is enabled. Flash softkey is provided Cisco IP phones 7940 and 7960 users on Foreign Exchange Office (FXO) lines attached to the Cisco CallManager Express system. 'true' means Flash soft key display on IP Phones is enabled. 'false' means that the Flash soft key on IP phones is not displayed in a Cisco CallManager Express system.

ccmeSecondaryDialTonePrefix.name: ccmeSecondaryDialTonePrefix
ccmeSecondaryDialTonePrefix.description: Indicates secondary dial tone access prefix digit string. If secondary dial tone is not configured on this device, in such case the object returns a zero length string. Example - 9.

ccmeWebAdminSystemUser.name: ccmeWebAdminSystemUser
ccmeWebAdminSystemUser.description: Indicates login username for a Cisco CallManager Express system administrator.

ccmeWebAdminCustomerUser.name: ccmeWebAdminCustomerUser
ccmeWebAdminCustomerUser.description: Indicates login username for a Cisco CallManager Express customer administrator.

ccmeSystemMessage.name: ccmeSystemMessage
ccmeSystemMessage.description: Indicates the configured text system message for display on idle Cisco IP phone 7940's and 7960's in a Cisco CallManager Express system. The text message is Alpha numeric string of up to 32 characters to disply when the phone is idle.

ccmeDialplanPatternTable.name: ccmeDialplanPatternTable
ccmeDialplanPatternTable.description: A list of Dialplan patterns configured on this device.

ccmeDialplanPatternEntry.name: ccmeDialplanPatternEntry
ccmeDialplanPatternEntry.description: Information on a dialplan pattern configured. There is an entry in this table for each Dialplan Pattern that is configured on this device.

ccmeDialplanPatternIndex.name: ccmeDialplanPatternIndex
ccmeDialplanPatternIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this ccmeDialplanPatternTable.

ccmeDialplanPatternTag.name: ccmeDialplanPatternTag
ccmeDialplanPatternTag.description: Indicates the number that identifies the dial-plan pattern.

ccmeDialplanExtLength.name: ccmeDialplanExtLength
ccmeDialplanExtLength.description: Indicates length of digit extension for Dial plan pattern extension.

ccmeDialplanPattern.name: ccmeDialplanPattern
ccmeDialplanPattern.description: Indicates string of digits forming a dial-plan pattern, such as the area code, the prefix, and the first one or two digits of the extension number, plus wild card markers or dots (.) for the remainder of the extension number digits. Example - 40854.....

ccmeDialplanExtPattern.name: ccmeDialplanExtPattern
ccmeDialplanExtPattern.description: Indicates string of digits forming the extension number leading digit pattern that are used when the leading digits of the extension number are different from the E.164 telephone number leading digits defined by the ccmeDialplanPattern object.

ccmeDialplanAllowRegiEnabled.name: ccmeDialplanAllowRegiEnabled
ccmeDialplanAllowRegiEnabled.description: Indicates whether the E.164 number in the dial peer is allowed to register with the gatekeeper. 'true' means that the registration is allowed. 'false' means that the registration is disabled.

ccmeKeepAliveTimeout.name: ccmeKeepAliveTimeout
ccmeKeepAliveTimeout.description: Indicates the length of time interval between successive keepalive messages from this device to IP phones.

ccmeInterDigitTimeout.name: ccmeInterDigitTimeout
ccmeInterDigitTimeout.description: Indicates the length of time interval for interdigit timeout for Cisco IP phones.

ccmeBusyTimeout.name: ccmeBusyTimeout
ccmeBusyTimeout.description: Indicates amount of wait time after which the call is disconnected from a busy signal.

ccmeAlertTimeout.name: ccmeAlertTimeout
ccmeAlertTimeout.description: Indicates the length of time interval for which Cisco CallManager Express allows the IP phone to alert (ring) if a call is not answered.

ccmeEphoneConfTable.name: ccmeEphoneConfTable
ccmeEphoneConfTable.description: A list of IP phones (Ephones or EthernetPhones) configured on this device.

ccmeEphoneConfEntry.name: ccmeEphoneConfEntry
ccmeEphoneConfEntry.description: Information about a configured IP phone. There is an entry in this table for each IP Phone that is configured on this device. An entry is deleted in this table once an IP Phone configuration is removed from this device.

ccmeEphoneTag.name: ccmeEphoneTag
ccmeEphoneTag.description: An number that uniquely identifies a IP phone configured on the device. The maximum number of Ephone entries varies among Cisco IOS platforms and may be less than 120.

ccmeEphoneIpAddressType.name: ccmeEphoneIpAddressType
ccmeEphoneIpAddressType.description: Address type of ccmeEphoneIpAddress. Only IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are expected.

ccmeEphoneIpAddress.name: ccmeEphoneIpAddress
ccmeEphoneIpAddress.description: Indicates the designated IP address to this Cisco IP phone (Ephone) configured on this device.

ccmeEphoneMacAddress.name: ccmeEphoneMacAddress
ccmeEphoneMacAddress.description: The MAC address of a Cisco IP phone.

ccmeEphoneModel.name: ccmeEphoneModel
ccmeEphoneModel.description: Type and model of Cisco IP phone.

ccmeEphoneUsername.name: ccmeEphoneUsername
ccmeEphoneUsername.description: Indicates the username of the local Cisco IP phone user. Default is 'Admin'. The login account allows a phone user to access a web-based GUI to view information and change some personal settings for the phone user's own phone only. A login account is also required for users of Telephony Application Programming Interface (TAPI) aware PC applications, which can register with this device and exercise remote-control operations of Cisco IP phones.

ccmeEphoneKeepAlive.name: ccmeEphoneKeepAlive
ccmeEphoneKeepAlive.description: Indicates the time interval between successive keepalive messages from this device to this particular IP phone. If the router fails to receive three successive keepalive messages, it considers the phone to be out of service until the phone re-registers.

ccmeEphoneAutoLineOut.name: ccmeEphoneAutoLineOut
ccmeEphoneAutoLineOut.description: Indicates the line (Ephone-DN) that will be selected for out going calls when this Cisco IP phone goes off-hook.

ccmeEphonePagingDn.name: ccmeEphonePagingDn
ccmeEphonePagingDn.description: Indicates the audio paging DN group configured for this Cisco IP phone.

ccmeEphoneAddon.name: ccmeEphoneAddon
ccmeEphoneAddon.description: Indicates the number of add on modules (Cisco IP phone 7914) that are attached to this phone.

ccmeEphoneTemplate.name: ccmeEphoneTemplate
ccmeEphoneTemplate.description: Indicates the Ephone template tag associated with this IP phone.

ccmeEphonePagingPolicy.name: ccmeEphonePagingPolicy
ccmeEphonePagingPolicy.description: Indicates paging mechanism associated with this Cisco IP phone. unicast(1) - Indicates the Cisco IP phone is not capable of receiving audio paging through multicast and requests that all pages to this phone be sent through unicast. multicast(2) - Audio paging is transmitted to the Cisco IP phone using multicast.

ccmeEphoneKeyPhone.name: ccmeEphoneKeyPhone
ccmeEphoneKeyPhone.description: Indicates whether the phone is marked as 'Key' IP phone. 'true' indicates IP phone is configured as Key IP phone. 'false' indicates IP phone is not configured as key IP phone.

ccmeEphoneAutoLineInEnabled.name: ccmeEphoneAutoLineInEnabled
ccmeEphoneAutoLineInEnabled.description: Indicates automatic line (Ephone-Dn) selection for incoming call is available. 'true' indicates automatic line selection for incoming calls is enabled. 'false' indicates auto-line selection for incoming calls on this Cisco IP phone is disabled.

ccmeEphoneAftHrsBlkExmptEnabled.name: ccmeEphoneAftHrsBlkExmptEnabled
ccmeEphoneAftHrsBlkExmptEnabled.description: Indicates whether this Cisco IP phone is exempt from after-hours blocking. 'true' indicates this Cisco IP phone is exempt from after-hour blocking. 'false' indicates is this Cisco IP phone is included in after-hour blocking.

ccmeEphoneNightBellSvcEnabled.name: ccmeEphoneNightBellSvcEnabled
ccmeEphoneNightBellSvcEnabled.description: Indicates night-bell service is available on this Cisco IP Phone. 'true' indicates night-bell service is enabled for this IP phone. 'false' indicates night-bell service is disabled.

ccmeEphoneKeepConfEnabled.name: ccmeEphoneKeepConfEnabled
ccmeEphoneKeepConfEnabled.description: Indicates whether the call would be disconnected when conference initiator hangs-up. 'true' - Indicates not to disconnect conference when conference initiator hangs-up. Connect remaining parties together directly using call transfer. 'false' - Disconnect conference when initiator hangs-up.

ccmeEphonePrimaryDn.name: ccmeEphonePrimaryDn
ccmeEphonePrimaryDn.description: This object indicates the primary extension DN (Ephone-Dn) for this Cisco IP phone. Zero value indicates no primary extension DN is set for this IP phone

ccmeEMUserProfileTag.name: ccmeEMUserProfileTag
ccmeEMUserProfileTag.description: This object indicates the user profile tag for this Cisco Extension Mobility IP phone. Zero value indicates no user logs into this phone.

ccmeEMLogOutProfileTag.name: ccmeEMLogOutProfileTag
ccmeEMLogOutProfileTag.description: This object indicates the logout profile tag configured for this Cisco Extension Mobility IP phone. Zero value indicates this phone is not an Extension Mobility phone.

ccmeEphoneSpeedDialConfTable.name: ccmeEphoneSpeedDialConfTable
ccmeEphoneSpeedDialConfTable.description: Information about configured speed dial entries for all IP phones.

ccmeEphoneSpeedDialConfEntry.name: ccmeEphoneSpeedDialConfEntry
ccmeEphoneSpeedDialConfEntry.description: Information about all configured speed dial entries for an IP phone. There is an entry created for each Speed Dial configured on this device. An entry is deleted from this table when the speed dial configuration is removed.

ccmeEphoneSpeedDialTableIndex.name: ccmeEphoneSpeedDialTableIndex
ccmeEphoneSpeedDialTableIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeEphoneSpeedDialConfEntry.

ccmeEphoneSpeedDialTag.name: ccmeEphoneSpeedDialTag
ccmeEphoneSpeedDialTag.description: An unique identifier tag configured for a speed-dial entry.

ccmeEphoneSpeedDialNumber.name: ccmeEphoneSpeedDialNumber
ccmeEphoneSpeedDialNumber.description: This object indicates the configured speed dial E.164 phone extension number that is associated with a line (ephone-dn) on this Cisco IP phone.

ccmeEphoneSpeedDialLabel.name: ccmeEphoneSpeedDialLabel
ccmeEphoneSpeedDialLabel.description: Indicates the text to be displayed next to the speed-dial button on Cisco IP Phone.

ccmeEphoneFastDialConfTable.name: ccmeEphoneFastDialConfTable
ccmeEphoneFastDialConfTable.description: Information about configured fast dial entries for all IP phones.

ccmeEphoneFastDialConfEntry.name: ccmeEphoneFastDialConfEntry
ccmeEphoneFastDialConfEntry.description: Information about all configured fast dial entries for an IP phone. There is an entry created in this table for each Fast dial configured on this device. An entry is deleted from this table when Fast dial configuration is removed from this device.

ccmeEphoneFastDialTableIndex.name: ccmeEphoneFastDialTableIndex
ccmeEphoneFastDialTableIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeEphoneFastDialConfEntry.

ccmeEphoneFastDialNumber.name: ccmeEphoneFastDialNumber
ccmeEphoneFastDialNumber.description: This object indicates the configured fast dial E.164 phone extension number that is associated with this Cisco IP phone. No primary number is associated as a default.

ccmeEphoneFastDialName.name: ccmeEphoneFastDialName
ccmeEphoneFastDialName.description: This object indicates the configured name associated with this fast dial E.164 phone extension number that is associated with this Cisco IP phone. When no name is associated, in that case this object will return a string length of zero.

ccmeEphoneBtnDNAssocConfTable.name: ccmeEphoneBtnDNAssocConfTable
ccmeEphoneBtnDNAssocConfTable.description: Information about all configured DN and button association for all IP phones.

ccmeEphoneBtnDNAssocConfEntry.name: ccmeEphoneBtnDNAssocConfEntry
ccmeEphoneBtnDNAssocConfEntry.description: Information about a configured DN and button association entries for an IP phone. There is an entry in this table for each DN and button association that is configured on this device. An entry is deleted once the configuration is deleted from this device.

ccmeEphoneButtonNumber.name: ccmeEphoneButtonNumber
ccmeEphoneButtonNumber.description: The button number of an IP phone.

ccmeEphoneOverlayDN.name: ccmeEphoneOverlayDN
ccmeEphoneOverlayDN.description: This object indicates the overlay DN's configured for this button on this IP phone.

ccmeEphoneDnConfigTable.name: ccmeEphoneDnConfigTable
ccmeEphoneDnConfigTable.description: A list of configured Ephone-DN's (Directory Number or extensions) for Cisco IP phone lines on this device.

ccmeEphoneDnConfigEntry.name: ccmeEphoneDnConfigEntry
ccmeEphoneDnConfigEntry.description: Information about each configured extension/DN. There is an entry in this table for each Ephone DN configured on this device. In SRST (Survivable Remote Site Telephone) mode, an entry is created for each Ephone-DN automatically generated. An entry is deleted from this table if the Ephone-DN is un-configured on this device.

ccmeEphoneDnTag.name: ccmeEphoneDnTag
ccmeEphoneDnTag.description: A unique sequence number that indicates an Cisco IP phone extension (ephone-dn) configured on this device.

ccmeEphoneDnType.name: ccmeEphoneDnType
ccmeEphoneDnType.description: Extension type of the line. extension(1) - Cisco IP Phone line. intercom(2) - Part of pair of intercom line. paging(3) - type to receive audio pages. moh(4) - type to address MoH. mwi(5) - type to address MWI. parkslot(6) - type to address call park slot. loopback(7) - loopback directory number.

ccmeEphoneDnMode.name: ccmeEphoneDnMode
ccmeEphoneDnMode.description: Mode of the line. single(1) - Single line mode. dual(2) - Dual line mode, that has one virtual voice port and two channels to handle two independent calls. This capacity allows call waiting, call transfer and conference functions within a single line (ephone-dn).

ccmeEphoneDnPriNum.name: ccmeEphoneDnPriNum
ccmeEphoneDnPriNum.description: Indicates the primary E.164 phone extension number that is associated with a line (ephone-dn) on this device. No primary number is associated as a default.

ccmeEphoneDnSecNum.name: ccmeEphoneDnSecNum
ccmeEphoneDnSecNum.description: Indicates the second E.164 phone extension number that is associated with a line (ephone-dn) on this device.

ccmeEphoneDnName.name: ccmeEphoneDnName
ccmeEphoneDnName.description: Indicates the name of the person associated with this extension (ephone-dn). If no specific name of person is associated with the IP phone, then this object will contain a zero-length string.

ccmeEphoneDnLabel.name: ccmeEphoneDnLabel
ccmeEphoneDnLabel.description: Indicates the text string that is displayed on the Cisco IP phone console instead of the extension phone number.

ccmeEphoneDnPriPref.name: ccmeEphoneDnPriPref
ccmeEphoneDnPriPref.description: This object shows the preference for the primary number associated with an extension. Range is from 0 to 10, where 0 is highest and 10 is lowest.

ccmeEphoneDnSecPref.name: ccmeEphoneDnSecPref
ccmeEphoneDnSecPref.description: This object shows the preference for the secondary number associated with an extension. Range is from 0 to 10, where 0 is highest and 10 is lowest.

ccmeEphoneDnCFBusyNum.name: ccmeEphoneDnCFBusyNum
ccmeEphoneDnCFBusyNum.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone number to which calls are forwarded for all the incoming calls to busy extension. If no specific call forwarding phone number is associated with the IP phone, then this object will contain a zero-length string.

ccmeEphoneDnCFAllNum.name: ccmeEphoneDnCFAllNum
ccmeEphoneDnCFAllNum.description: Indicates the E.164 phone number to which calls are forwarded for all the incoming calls to an extension (ephone-dn). If no specific call forwarding all phone number is associated with the IP phone, then this object will contain a zero-length string.

ccmeEphoneDnCFNoAnNum.name: ccmeEphoneDnCFNoAnNum
ccmeEphoneDnCFNoAnNum.description: Indicates the E.164 phone number to which calls are forwarded for all the incoming calls to an extension (ephone-dn) that does not answer. If no specific call forwarding number when extension does not answer is associated, then this object will contain a zero-length string.

ccmeEphoneDnCFNoAnTo.name: ccmeEphoneDnCFNoAnTo
ccmeEphoneDnCFNoAnTo.description: Indicates the duration that a call can ring with no answer before the call is forwarded to another extension/line/DN.

ccmeEphoneDnMwiCapability.name: ccmeEphoneDnMwiCapability
ccmeEphoneDnMwiCapability.description: Indicates the capability of an extension (ephone-dn) to process message-waiting indication (MWI) notification from an external voice-messaging systems. mwiOn - Extension can process MWI ON notifications using either the main or secondary phone number. mwiOff - Extension can process MWI OFF notifications using either the main or secondary phone number. mwiOnOff - Extension can process both MWI ON and OFF notifications using either the main or secondary phone number. mwiDisabled - MWI notifications are disabled on an extension.

ccmeEphoneDnHuntstop.name: ccmeEphoneDnHuntstop
ccmeEphoneDnHuntstop.description: Indicates the call hunting behavior for an extension (ephone-dn). If the value of this object is 'true', an incoming call does not roll over (hunt) to another ephone-dn if the called ephone-dn is busy or does not answer and a hunting strategy has been established that includes this ephone-dn.

ccmeEphoneDnHuntstopCh.name: ccmeEphoneDnHuntstopCh
ccmeEphoneDnHuntstopCh.description: Indicates the call hunting behavior for an extension (ephone-dn) channel. If this object is enabled on dual-line extensions, an incoming call does not roll over (hunt) to another channel if the first channel is busy or does not answer on this ephone-dn.

ccmeEphoneDnHoldAltTo.name: ccmeEphoneDnHoldAltTo
ccmeEphoneDnHoldAltTo.description: Indicates time out for repeating audible alert notification when a call is on hold on a Cisco IP phone. Range is 15 to 300. By default hold alert feature is disabled. In such case, this object will return a zero value.

ccmeEphoneDnHoldAltType.name: ccmeEphoneDnHoldAltType
ccmeEphoneDnHoldAltType.description: Indicates when hold alert audible notification will be repeated on a Cisco IP phone. idle(1) - Alerts only when the Cisco IP phone is idle. originator(2) - Alerts when the Cisco IP phone is idle or busy. shared(3) - Alerts only when the Cisco IP phone is idle but alerts all phones that share the line.

ccmeEphoneDnMwiSipSubscrEnabled.name: ccmeEphoneDnMwiSipSubscrEnabled
ccmeEphoneDnMwiSipSubscrEnabled.description: Indicates whether this extension (DN) in a Cisco CallManager Express system is subscribed to a SIP-based MWI server. 'true' indicates this extension can receive MWI from SIP-based MWI server. 'false' indicates extension is not subscribed to receive MWI.

ccmeEphoneDnScriptName.name: ccmeEphoneDnScriptName
ccmeEphoneDnScriptName.description: Indicates the session-level IVR application script in Tool Command Language (TCL) for this extension (ephone-dn) in CCME system. By default no application script is selected for an extension and the object length in this case will return a string of zero length.

ccmeNotificationEnable.name: ccmeNotificationEnable
ccmeNotificationEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the Cisco CallManager Express notifications. When this variable is 'true', generation of CCME notifications are enabled. When this variable is 'false', generation of CCME notifications is disabled.

ccmeSysTrapSeverity.name: ccmeSysTrapSeverity
ccmeSysTrapSeverity.description: The internally-defined severity of the particular alarm condition, associated with the most recent notification. A subsequent event in which the alarm condition changes from its failed state back to a 'normal' state has a severity of 'clear'.

ccmeSysNotificationReason.name: ccmeSysNotificationReason
ccmeSysNotificationReason.description: The internally-defined failure cause of the particular alarm condition, associated with the most recent trap.

ccmeEphoneUnRegThreshold.name: ccmeEphoneUnRegThreshold
ccmeEphoneUnRegThreshold.description: This variable sets the threshold to limit the unregistration trap notification.

ccmeEphoneTrapReason.name: ccmeEphoneTrapReason
ccmeEphoneTrapReason.description: The internally-defined failure cause of the particular alarm condition, associated with the most recent Ephone trap.

ccmeUserAutoLogoutTo.name: ccmeUserAutoLogoutTo
ccmeUserAutoLogoutTo.description: Indicates the length of time before the users of IP phones in a Cisco CallManager Express system are automatically logged out.

ccmeUserLoginDeactivateTime.name: ccmeUserLoginDeactivateTime
ccmeUserLoginDeactivateTime.description: Indicates the specified time of day when user logins for all IP phones are deactivated.

ccmeMwiSipServerIpAddress.name: ccmeMwiSipServerIpAddress
ccmeMwiSipServerIpAddress.description: Indicates the designated IP address to an external SIP based message-waiting indication (MWI) server. The type of this address is determined by the value of the ccmeSysIPAddressType object.

ccmeMwiSipServerTransportType.name: ccmeMwiSipServerTransportType
ccmeMwiSipServerTransportType.description: Indicates the transport layer protocol used to connect external SIP-based message-waiting indication (MWI) server. tcp(1) - TCP as transport layer protocol. udp(2) - UDP as transport layer protocol.

ccmeMwiSipServerPortNumber.name: ccmeMwiSipServerPortNumber
ccmeMwiSipServerPortNumber.description: Indicates the port number for the message-waiting indication (MWI) server.

ccmeMwiSipServerRegE164Enabled.name: ccmeMwiSipServerRegE164Enabled
ccmeMwiSipServerRegE164Enabled.description: Indicates whether E.164 number is registered with SIP proxy or Registrar rather than an extension number. 'true' indicates E.164 is registered. 'false' indicates extension number is registered.

ccmeMwiSipSvrUnsolicitedEnabled.name: ccmeMwiSipSvrUnsolicitedEnabled
ccmeMwiSipSvrUnsolicitedEnabled.description: Indicates whether SIP NOTIFY for MWI is sent without a SUBSCRIBE from the Cisco CallManager Express. 'true' indicates SIP NOTIFY is sent without SIP SUBSCRIBE. 'false' indicates solicited NOTIFY is sent.

ccmeCorConfTable.name: ccmeCorConfTable
ccmeCorConfTable.description: A list of Class of Restriction (COR) configured on this device.

ccmeCorConfEntry.name: ccmeCorConfEntry
ccmeCorConfEntry.description: Information about a Class of restriction (COR) configured entry. There is an entry for each COR configured on this device. An entry is deleted if the COR is removed from configuration.

ccmeCorTableIndex.name: ccmeCorTableIndex
ccmeCorTableIndex.description: An arbitrary and unique index for this CcmeCorConfEntry.

ccmeCorTag.name: ccmeCorTag
ccmeCorTag.description: Indicates the tag number. If ccmeEnabled object is 'true' for Cisco CallManager Express Mode then this object indicates the ephone-dn tag under which the COR was configured. If csrstEnabled object is 'true' for Cisco Survivable Remote Site Telephony (SRST) mode, then this object indicates the COR list identifier configured under SRST configuration or Voice Registrar configuration.

ccmeCorListName.name: ccmeCorListName
ccmeCorListName.description: Indicates the COR list name configured on this device.

ccmeCorScope.name: ccmeCorScope
ccmeCorScope.description: Indicates the scope of this COR list for a list of associated dial-peers. ccme(1) - indicates this COR is applicable to the dial-peer associated with ciscoCorTag Ephone-DN object. srstSccp(2) - indicates this COR is applicable to all the dynamically created dial-peers under SCCP SRST mode. srstSip(3) - indicates this COR is applicable to all the SIP SRST dial-peers that belong to a specified voice registrar pool indicated by ciscoCorVoiceRegPoolNumber object.

ccmeCorDirection.name: ccmeCorDirection
ccmeCorDirection.description: Indicates whether the COR will be used by incoming or outgoing dial peers.

ccmeCorStartingNumber.name: ccmeCorStartingNumber
ccmeCorStartingNumber.description: Indicates the starting number of a range of directory numbers for a COR list configured on this device.

ccmeCorEndingNumber.name: ccmeCorEndingNumber
ccmeCorEndingNumber.description: Indicates the ending number of a range of directory numbers for a COR list configured on this device.

ccmeCorVoiceRegPoolNumber.name: ccmeCorVoiceRegPoolNumber
ccmeCorVoiceRegPoolNumber.description: Indicates the voice registrar pool number under which this COR list is applied.

ccmeCorListDefaultEnabled.name: ccmeCorListDefaultEnabled
ccmeCorListDefaultEnabled.description: Indicates whether the default COR list is enabled or disabled for this COR entry. 'true' indicates this COR list assumes behavior of a pre-defined default COR list. 'false' indicates default COR list is not applied.

ccmeLoopbackDnConfTable.name: ccmeLoopbackDnConfTable
ccmeLoopbackDnConfTable.description: A list of loopback DN's (lines) configured on this device.

ccmeLoopbackDnConfEntry.name: ccmeLoopbackDnConfEntry
ccmeLoopbackDnConfEntry.description: Information about a loopback DN configured on this device. There is an entry created for each loopback DN configured on this device. An entry is deleted if the loopback DN is removed from this device configuration.

ccmeLoopbackDnTag.name: ccmeLoopbackDnTag
ccmeLoopbackDnTag.description: A unique sequence number that identifies the ephone-dn loopback pairs in this device.

ccmeLoopbackDnforward.name: ccmeLoopbackDnforward
ccmeLoopbackDnforward.description: Indicates the number of digits in the original called number that will be forwarded to the other phone-dn in the loopback-dn pair.

ccmeLoopbackDnStrip.name: ccmeLoopbackDnStrip
ccmeLoopbackDnStrip.description: Indicates the number of leading digits that will be stripped from the original called number that will be forwarded to the other phone-dn in the loopback-dn pair.

ccmeLoopbackDnPrefix.name: ccmeLoopbackDnPrefix
ccmeLoopbackDnPrefix.description: Indicates the string of digits that will be added in the front of the forwarded called number.

ccmeLoopbackDnSuffix.name: ccmeLoopbackDnSuffix
ccmeLoopbackDnSuffix.description: Indicates the string of digits that will be added in the end of the forwarded called number.

ccmeLoopbackDnRetryTo.name: ccmeLoopbackDnRetryTo
ccmeLoopbackDnRetryTo.description: Indicates the number of seconds to wait before retrying the loopback target when it is busy or unavailable. A zero-value indicates that retry is disabled and appropriate call-progress tones are passed to the call originator.

ccmeLoopbackDnAutoCon.name: ccmeLoopbackDnAutoCon
ccmeLoopbackDnAutoCon.description: Indicates whether the automatic connection capability for the call during far-end alert. 'true' indicates call is immediately connected and in-band alerting is provided while waiting for the far-end destination to answer. 'false' indicates automatic connection is disabled.

ccmeLoopbackDnCodec.name: ccmeLoopbackDnCodec
ccmeLoopbackDnCodec.description: The codec type applied to the calls that pass through the loopback-dn. g711alaw(1) - indicates the G.711 a-law is applied. g711ulaw(2) - indicates the G.711 mu-law is applied. Option 1 and 2 overrides the G.711 codec type that is negotiated for the call and provides mu-law to a-law conversion if needed. default(3) - indicates the Real-Time Transport Protocol (RTP) voice packets are passed through the loopback-dn without considering the G.711 coding type negotiated for the calls.

ccmeIntercomDnConfTable.name: ccmeIntercomDnConfTable
ccmeIntercomDnConfTable.description: A list of intercom DN's (lines) configured on this device.

ccmeIntercomDnConfEntry.name: ccmeIntercomDnConfEntry
ccmeIntercomDnConfEntry.description: Information about a intercom DN configured on this device. There is an entry created for each intercom DN configured on this device. An entry is deleted if the intercom DN is removed from this device configuration.

ccmeIntercomDnTag.name: ccmeIntercomDnTag
ccmeIntercomDnTag.description: Indicates Ephone-DN (line) tag number under which this Intercom was configured.

ccmeIntercomDnExtensionNum.name: ccmeIntercomDnExtensionNum
ccmeIntercomDnExtensionNum.description: Indicates the telephone number to which intercom calls are placed.

ccmeIntercomDnBargeInEnabled.name: ccmeIntercomDnBargeInEnabled
ccmeIntercomDnBargeInEnabled.description: Indicates whether the inbound intercom calls behavior when existing call is active. 'true' indicates inbound intercom calls force the existing call into call-hold state and allows the intercom call to be answered immediately. 'false' indicates inbound intercom calls don't barge-in the existing calls.

ccmeIntercomDnAutoAnsEnabled.name: ccmeIntercomDnAutoAnsEnabled
ccmeIntercomDnAutoAnsEnabled.description: Indicates whether the auto-answer feature is applied to this EPhone-DN. 'true' indicates auto-answer feature is enabled. 'false' indicates auto-answer feature is disabled. This indicates the Ephone-DN a connection that resembles a private line, automatic ringdown (PLAR).

ccmeIntercomDnLabel.name: ccmeIntercomDnLabel
ccmeIntercomDnLabel.description: Indicates the label for the intercom configured on this device.

ccmeMohMulticastIpAddressType.name: ccmeMohMulticastIpAddressType
ccmeMohMulticastIpAddressType.description: Address type of ccmeMohMulticastIpAddress. Only IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are expected.

ccmeMohMulticastIpAddress.name: ccmeMohMulticastIpAddress
ccmeMohMulticastIpAddress.description: This object indicates the destination IP address for multicast of the Music-on-hold audio stream. The type of this address is determined by the value of the ccmeSysIPAddressType object.

ccmeMohMulticastPortNumber.name: ccmeMohMulticastPortNumber
ccmeMohMulticastPortNumber.description: This object indicates the media port for multicast of the Music-oh-hold audio stream.

ccmeMohMulticastRoute.name: ccmeMohMulticastRoute
ccmeMohMulticastRoute.description: Indicates a string of IP addresses, each separate by other by a space, over which Music-oh-hold IP multicast packets are transmitted.

ccmeEMUserDirNumConfTable.name: ccmeEMUserDirNumConfTable
ccmeEMUserDirNumConfTable.description: A list of Directory Number or extensions configured under user profile which are downloaded to Cisco IP extension mobility phones when an user log into it using this user profile.

ccmeEMUserDirNumConfEntry.name: ccmeEMUserDirNumConfEntry
ccmeEMUserDirNumConfEntry.description: Information about each directory number configured under user profile to be downloaded to an extension mobility IP phone when an user logs into it using this user profile. There is an entry in this table for each line on the logged in ephone.

ccmEMUserProfileDirNumIndex.name: ccmEMUserProfileDirNumIndex
ccmEMUserProfileDirNumIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies an Extension Mobility user profile.

ccmeEMUserDirNumTag.name: ccmeEMUserDirNumTag
ccmeEMUserDirNumTag.description: A number that uniquely identifies a directory number entry.

ccmeEMUserDirNum.name: ccmeEMUserDirNum
ccmeEMUserDirNum.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone diretory or extension number which is downloaded to a line on the extension mobility phone when an user logs into it.

ccmeEMUserDirNumOverlay.name: ccmeEMUserDirNumOverlay
ccmeEMUserDirNumOverlay.description: This object indicates the overlay directory number configured for this line under this user profile.

ccmeEMLogoutDirNumConfTable.name: ccmeEMLogoutDirNumConfTable
ccmeEMLogoutDirNumConfTable.description: A list of Directory Number or extensions configured under logout profile which are downloaded to Cisco IP extension mobility phones when an user log out or no one is logged in.

ccmeEMLogoutDirNumConfEntry.name: ccmeEMLogoutDirNumConfEntry
ccmeEMLogoutDirNumConfEntry.description: Information about each directory number configured under logout profile to be downloaded to an extension mobility IP phone at logout state. There is an entry in this table for each line on the ephone at logout state. There is an entry in this table for each logout profile.

ccmEMLogOutProfileDirNumIndex.name: ccmEMLogOutProfileDirNumIndex
ccmEMLogOutProfileDirNumIndex.description: A number that uniquely identifies an Extension Mobility logout profile.

ccmeEMLogoutDirNumTag.name: ccmeEMLogoutDirNumTag
ccmeEMLogoutDirNumTag.description: A number that uniquely identifies a directory number entry.

ccmeEMLogoutDirNum.name: ccmeEMLogoutDirNum
ccmeEMLogoutDirNum.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone diretory or extension number which is downloaded to a line on the extension mobility phone at the logout state.

ccmeEMLogoutDirNumOverlay.name: ccmeEMLogoutDirNumOverlay
ccmeEMLogoutDirNumOverlay.description: This object indicates the overlay directory number configured for this line under this logout profile.

ccmeEphoneCallLegs.name: ccmeEphoneCallLegs
ccmeEphoneCallLegs.description: Indicates the active number of call legs contributed from the Cisco IP Phones and TAPI clients interacting with this device at this instance.

ccmeEphoneTot.name: ccmeEphoneTot
ccmeEphoneTot.description: Indicates the total number of Cisco IP phones (Ephones) seen by this device since the last reset.

ccmeEphoneTotRegistered.name: ccmeEphoneTotRegistered
ccmeEphoneTotRegistered.description: Indicates the total number of Cisco IP phones currently registered to this device.

ccmeEphoneTotKeyPhConfigured.name: ccmeEphoneTotKeyPhConfigured
ccmeEphoneTotKeyPhConfigured.description: Indicates the total number of configured Cisco IP phones that are marked as Key phones on this device.

ccmeEphoneTotKeyPhRegistered.name: ccmeEphoneTotKeyPhRegistered
ccmeEphoneTotKeyPhRegistered.description: Indicates the total number of Key Cisco IP phones currently registered to this device.

ccmeEphoneActTable.name: ccmeEphoneActTable
ccmeEphoneActTable.description: A list of all IP phones currently registered on this device.

ccmeEphoneActEntry.name: ccmeEphoneActEntry
ccmeEphoneActEntry.description: Information about an IP phone seen by this device. There is an entry added for each new IP phone registration in this table. Entry is removed once the phone is deceased or re-registered.

ccmeEphoneDeviceName.name: ccmeEphoneDeviceName
ccmeEphoneDeviceName.description: Type and model of Cisco IP phone as seen in the registration on this device.

ccmeEphoneRegState.name: ccmeEphoneRegState
ccmeEphoneRegState.description: The registration state of the Cisco IP phone. registered(1) - indicates the phone is active. unregistered(2) - indicates the connection to Cisco IP phone was closed in normal manner. deceased(3) - indicates the connection to the Cisco IP phone was closed because of a keep-alive timeout.

ccmeEphoneActiveDN.name: ccmeEphoneActiveDN
ccmeEphoneActiveDN.description: Current active DN (line) on the IP phone.

ccmeEphoneActivityStatus.name: ccmeEphoneActivityStatus
ccmeEphoneActivityStatus.description: Current status of the Cisco IP phone as seen on this device. onhook(1) - Phone is on-hook. offhook(2) - Phone is off-hook. ringing(3) - Phone is ringing. paging(4) - Phone is receiving an audio page.

ccmeEphoneKeepAliveCnt.name: ccmeEphoneKeepAliveCnt
ccmeEphoneKeepAliveCnt.description: Number of keepalive messages received from the Cisco IP phone by this device since the phone registered.

ccmeEphonePendingReset.name: ccmeEphonePendingReset
ccmeEphonePendingReset.description: Pending reset operation on this IP phone as seen by this device. True indicating reset is pending.

ccmeEphoneRegTime.name: ccmeEphoneRegTime
ccmeEphoneRegTime.description: Time this phone registered to this device.

ccmeEphoneCurrentFirmwareRev.name: ccmeEphoneCurrentFirmwareRev
ccmeEphoneCurrentFirmwareRev.description: The current vendor-specific firmware version string provided by the Cisco IP phone during registration on this device.

ccmeEphonePreviousFirmwareRev.name: ccmeEphonePreviousFirmwareRev
ccmeEphonePreviousFirmwareRev.description: The previous vendor-specific firmware version of Cisco IP phone provided by the Cisco IP phone during registration on this device.

ccmeEphoneLastError.name: ccmeEphoneLastError
ccmeEphoneLastError.description: Reason for last reset of the phone as seen by this device. Reason for last reset of phone could be 'TCP-timeout' or 'CallManager-closed-TCP' or 'Initialized'.

ccmeEphoneObservedType.name: ccmeEphoneObservedType
ccmeEphoneObservedType.description: Type and model of Cisco IP phone received by this device during the registration of IP phone.

ccmeEphoneLoginStatus.name: ccmeEphoneLoginStatus
ccmeEphoneLoginStatus.description: True indicates that a phone user is currently logged in on this phone. False indicates no phone user currently logged in on this phone.

ccmeEphoneDnDStatus.name: ccmeEphoneDnDStatus
ccmeEphoneDnDStatus.description: True indicates that phone is set do-not-disturb (DnD) on one or more of the phone's extensions used by the Cisco IP phone. False indicates no DnD is set.

ccmeEphoneDebugStatus.name: ccmeEphoneDebugStatus
ccmeEphoneDebugStatus.description: True indicates that phone is set in debug mode. False indicates no debug is disabled on this IP phone.

ccmeEphoneMediaActive.name: ccmeEphoneMediaActive
ccmeEphoneMediaActive.description: True indicates that phone is in active conversation. False indicates no conversation is ongoing.

ccmeEphoneTAPIClient.name: ccmeEphoneTAPIClient
ccmeEphoneTAPIClient.description: True indicates that phone is a TAPI client. False indicates the phone is not TAPI client.

ccmeEphoneMediaCapability.name: ccmeEphoneMediaCapability
ccmeEphoneMediaCapability.description: Indicates whether the registered IP phone is capable of supporting audio or video. audioOnly(1) - IP phone is only audio capable. audioVideo(2) - IP phone is audio and video capable.

ccmeEphoneRemote.name: ccmeEphoneRemote
ccmeEphoneRemote.description: True indicates that phone is suspected not to be on the local area network(LAN). This is derived from the ARP entry not seen on this device. False indicates the phone is in the same LAN as device.

ccmeMohSource.name: ccmeMohSource
ccmeMohSource.description: Cisco CallManager Express system can derive music-on-hold (MOH) from two locations. If flash (1) is displayed, the router is currently picking MOH stream from an audio file configured in flash file system. The location of the file is provided by ccmeMohFlashFile object. If liveFeed (2) is displayed, the router is currently picking MOH stream from an incoming call audio stream. Normally, a single ephone-dn would be configured to accept liveFeed call. ccmeEphoneDnType with moh type will specify this DN.

ccmeNightServiceEnabled.name: ccmeNightServiceEnabled
ccmeNightServiceEnabled.description: Indicates the current Night service state. 'true' means that Night service is active. 'false' means that Night service is inactive.

ccmeEMphoneTot.name: ccmeEMphoneTot
ccmeEMphoneTot.description: Indicates the total number of Cisco IP Extension Mobility phones (EMphones) seen by this device since the last reset.

ccmeEMphoneTotRegistered.name: ccmeEMphoneTotRegistered
ccmeEMphoneTotRegistered.description: This object indicates the total number of Cisco IP Extension Mobility phones registered to this CCME.

ccmeEphoneDnChStatsHistoryTable.name: ccmeEphoneDnChStatsHistoryTable
ccmeEphoneDnChStatsHistoryTable.description: A list of statistics for all Ephone-DN's (lines) on this device.

ccmeEphoneDnChStatsHistoryEntry.name: ccmeEphoneDnChStatsHistoryEntry
ccmeEphoneDnChStatsHistoryEntry.description: Statistical information about an Ephone-DN. There is an entry added for each new Ephone-DN configured in this table. Entry is removed once the Ephone-DN is removed from this device configuration.

ccmeEphoneDnChNum.name: ccmeEphoneDnChNum
ccmeEphoneDnChNum.description: The Ephone-DN (line) channel number for this entry.

ccmeEphoneDnChIncoming.name: ccmeEphoneDnChIncoming
ccmeEphoneDnChIncoming.description: Total number of incoming calls received by this Ephone-DN (line) channel.

ccmeEphoneDnChInAnswered.name: ccmeEphoneDnChInAnswered
ccmeEphoneDnChInAnswered.description: Total number of incoming calls answered by this Ephone-DN (line) channel.

ccmeEphoneDnChOutbound.name: ccmeEphoneDnChOutbound
ccmeEphoneDnChOutbound.description: Total number of calls placed by this Ephone-DN (line) channel.

ccmeEphoneDnChOutAnswered.name: ccmeEphoneDnChOutAnswered
